The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, July 19, 2004 				 Confession of killer friends
																								Howrah, July 18: Sampad Mukherjee and Arijit Pal, the two friends of Kuntal Sain who allegedly kidnapped him for money and killed him when the plan went awry, will confess before the subdivisional judicial magistrate here tomorrow.																								Sain, 18, was hacked to death on the night of July 2. Sampads mother and elder brother Jyotirmoy were also arrested for conniving with the duo. Fatal football clash																								Jadav Ghosh, 46, was killed and three others injured in a clash during a football match at Murshidabads Beldanga. The match between old rivals Makrampur Bakalipara clubs turned violent following a referees decision.
